definition.value: A 3-oxoacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-methylacetoacetic acid.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and D-galactitol joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A short-chain, methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA having 2-methylbutanoyl as the S-acyl group.
A short-chain, methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA that is the S-isobutyryl derivative of coenzyme A.
A beta-D-Galp-(1->2)-D-Glcp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
